## 6. Technical Approach

### 6.1 System Architecture

**Mobile App:** React Native (cross-platform iOS & Android)

**Backend:** Node.js (Express) + PostgreSQL database

**AI Services:** OpenAI GPT-4 API for chat + Custom BERT model for crisis detection

**Cloud Infrastructure:** AWS (EC2, RDS, S3)

**Security:** End-to-end encryption, TLS 1.3, GDPR/HIPAA compliant

### 6.2 Data Architecture

**Key Data Models:**
- User profiles (anonymous)
- Mood check-ins (encrypted)
- Workload logs
- Family pressure assessments
- Safety plans
- Chat history (encrypted)
- Peer support posts (moderated)

### 6.3 AI/ML Implementation

**AI Chat:**
- GPT-4 API with custom system prompts
- Empathetic, non-diagnostic responses
- Crisis keyword detection
- Safety filters

**Crisis Detection Model:**
- Fine-tuned BERT for text classification
- Training data: Annotated mental health crisis text
- Accuracy target: 95%+ for crisis detection
- Real-time inference (<500ms)

### 6.4 Privacy & Security

**Encryption:**
- AES-256 at rest
- TLS 1.3 in transit
- SQLCipher on device

**Access Controls:**
- Users access only own data
- Moderators access flagged content only
- No employer or family access

**Compliance:**
- GDPR (right to access, deletion, portability)
- India DPDP Act (data localization, consent)
- HIPAA (if applicable in US market)

---

## 7. Feature Specifications

### 7.1 Daily Mood & Emotional Check-In

**Purpose:** Early detection of emotional distress

**Implementation:**
- Emoji-based mood scale (😊 to 😢)
- Stress level (1-5)
- Work and family impact questions
- Optional free-text note

**Early Detection Logic:**
- 3+ days of severe mood → Suggest support
- 5+ days of high stress → Burnout warning
- Crisis keywords → Immediate intervention

### 7.2 AI-Based Emotional Support Chat

**Purpose:** Immediate empathetic listening

**Implementation:**
- 24/7 availability
- GPT-4 powered responses
- Crisis detection and escalation
- Clear disclaimers (not a therapist)

**Example Interaction:**
- User: "I'm so tired. I can't do this anymore."
- AI: "I hear you. Feeling exhausted and overwhelmed is really hard. Your feelings are completely valid. Would you like to talk about what's making you feel this way?"

### 7.3 Emergency Support Button 🚨

**Purpose:** One-tap crisis intervention

**Implementation:**
- Prominent on all screens
- Direct call to crisis helplines (AASRA, Vandrevala Foundation)
- Trusted contact notification
- Safety plan access

**Follow-Up:**
- 24-hour check-in notification
- Professional help suggestions
- Continued support

### 7.4 Other Features

**Workload Stress Tracker:** Log hours, detect burnout patterns

**Family Pressure Assessment:** Weekly reflective questions, journaling

**Guided Mental Health Tools:** Breathing exercises, grounding, journaling prompts

**Peer Support Community:** Anonymous discussion rooms, moderated content

**Self-Care Plan:** Personalized recommendations based on data

**Progress Tracker:** Visualize mood trends, celebrate milestones

---

## 8. Ethical & Safety Framework

### 8.1 Core Ethical Principles

1. **User Safety First:** Emotional and physical safety is absolute priority
2. **Transparency:** Clear communication about capabilities and limitations
3. **Autonomy:** Users control their data and choices
4. **Non-Maleficence:** Do no harm through design or content
5. **Professional Boundaries:** Complement, never replace, professional care

### 8.2 Crisis Intervention Protocol

**Multi-Layer Detection:**
1. Keyword detection ("suicide," "kill myself")
2. ML model (BERT-based, 85%+ accuracy)
3. Pattern analysis (severe mood decline)

**Immediate Response:**
- Emergency resources screen (<5 seconds)
- Crisis helplines (one-tap call)
- Trusted contacts
- Safety plan

**Post-Crisis Follow-Up:**
- 24-hour check-in
- Professional help suggestions
- Continued monitoring

### 8.3 Privacy Protection

**Data Minimization:** Collect only necessary data

**Encryption:** AES-256 at rest, TLS 1.3 in transit

**User Rights:**
- Right to access (export data)
- Right to deletion (one-click account deletion)
- Right to portability

**No Sharing:**
- Never shared with employers, family, insurance
- Anonymized data only for research (opt-in)

### 8.4 Content Moderation

**Peer Support Community:**
- Automated filters (profanity, hate speech, graphic content)
- Human moderators (review within 1 hour)
- Community guidelines enforcement
- Appeal process

---

## 9. UI/UX Design

### 9.1 Design Philosophy

**Calm, Not Clinical:** Warm, approachable aesthetic

**Safe, Not Scary:** No alarming visuals or language

**Simple, Not Simplistic:** Minimal cognitive load, clear hierarchy

**Empathetic, Not Patronizing:** Respectful, validating tone

### 9.2 Color Palette

**Primary:** Calming Blue (#4A90E2) - Trust, calm, stability

**Secondary:** Soft Teal (#5DADE2) - Healing, balance

**Success:** Gentle Green (#6FCF97) - Growth, hope

**Warning:** Warm Orange (#F6AD55) - Attention without panic

**Crisis:** Red (#E53E3E) - Emergency button only

### 9.3 Typography

**Primary Font:** Inter (UI elements)

**Secondary Font:** Lora (Headings, emotional content)

**Accessibility:** WCAG 2.1 AA compliant, scalable up to 200%

### 9.4 Key Design Elements

**Mood Selector:** Emoji-based, large tap targets

**Emergency Button:** Prominent, red, always accessible

**Cards:** Soft shadows, rounded corners, calming

**Animations:** Gentle, non-jarring transitions

