## 12. Social Impact Assessment

### 12.1 Target Population

**Primary:** 50 million early-career individuals in India (ages 20-30)

**Secondary:** Families, employers, mental health professionals

### 12.2 Expected Impact

**Individual Level:**
- Reduced emotional distress and burnout
- Increased awareness of mental health
- Earlier intervention before crisis
- Improved coping skills
- Reduced suicide attempts

**Societal Level:**
- Normalized mental health conversations
- Reduced stigma
- Increased professional help-seeking
- Improved workplace productivity
- Reduced healthcare costs (prevention vs. treatment)

